<concept id="AFARS_Appendix-EE_9-1">
      <title>
      <ph props="autonumber">9-1.</ph> Required Sources</title>
      <conbody>
        <p outputclass="List1">a. Cardholders must purchase in accordance with
the priorities set forth in <xref format="html"
               href="https://www.acquisition.gov/far/part-8"
               scope="external">
            <u>FAR Part
8</u>

          </xref>, along with use of mandatory sources (i.e., inventories
of the requiring agency, excess from other agencies, FPI supplies
on the <xref format="html"
               href="https://www.abilityone.gov/procurement_list/index.html"
               scope="external">Procurement
List</xref> maintained by AbilityOne, wholesale supply sources,
services on the <xref format="html"
               href="https://www.abilityone.gov/procurement_list/index.html"
               scope="external">Procurement
List</xref> maintained by AbilityOne, and other mandatory sources as
specified in <xref format="html"
               href="https://www.acquisition.gov/far/8.003"
               scope="external">FAR
8.003</xref>) or optional sources (i.e., FSS; Governmentwide
acquisition contracts; multi-agency contracts; any other
procurement instruments intended for use by multiple agencies,
including BPAs under FSS contracts; FPI; and commercial sources
(including educational and nonprofit institutions) in the open
market).</p>
        <p outputclass="List1">b. <b>Coordinated Acquisition
Assignments</b>. Requiring activities must obtain the assigned
supplies listed in <xref format="html"
               href="https://www.acquisition.gov/dfarspgi/pgi-208.7006-coordinated-acquisition-assignments."
               scope="external">DFARS
PGI 208.7006</xref> from the Component responsible to supply the
commodity through use of a MIPR as prescribed in <xref format="html"
               href="https://www.acq.osd.mil/dpap/dars/dfars/html/current/208_70.htm#208.7002"
               scope="external">
            <u>DFARS
208.7002</u>
          </xref> and <xref format="html"
               href="https://www.acq.osd.mil/dpap/dars/pgi/pgi_htm/current/PGI208_70.htm"
               scope="external">
            <u>DFARS
PGI 208.7004</u>
          </xref>. Examples of assigned commodities include
flags/pennants, badges/insignia, tents, weapons, ammunition, and
explosives.</p>
